&quot;Let’s suppose this equates out to a direct increase in damage of 4% average. &quot;<br>
<br>
You entire argument is flawed. You can't 'suppose' something like this. A 4% increase in ATK does not necessarily mean a 4% increase in damage. I suggest you try some hard data, this argument is completely invalidated by this supposition.<br>
<br>
To make things more simple:<br>
VoG = 58% Haste<br>
ToV Level Haste = 41%ish<br>
= 99% Haste<br>
<br>
Shissar + decent haste = 100% haste<br>
<br>
So now you're talking would you rather have 99% haste and +ATK or 100% Haste and +AC?<br>
<br>
Your overall DPS (damage per second) will be higher with the 99% Haste and Bonus ATK, this will especially come into play on many of the new mobs that have much higher AC than previously encountered mobs, where ATK will allow you to hit for more tha minimum damage far more often. <p><img src=http://www.netcom.com/~rennyn/newkanyu.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uinfuryated.showPublicProfile?language=EN>inFURYated</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.albert.hoffpauir.com/everquest/images/sphere[1].gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tad-pole</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(3/5/02 11:03:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1101.topic&index=39>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ATK vs. Number of attacks per second.</span><hr size=1> Karadin,<br>
