Now I know you used extremes in the numbers to show your point but really it all comes down to averages. If SoS raises all your hits by X% then you will see more max hits as well. If VoG raises your damage per hit by X% then the end results will still be a increase of X% from both buffs. It just looks like VoG is doing more because it is easier to SEE the damage per hit then it is to count the number of hits you are doing per second or minute or mob.<br>
